                <note rend="inline" type="source">850d.00/362: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-19T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1919—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 19—2:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1688. Your 1458. For Phillips. You may say to the Norwegian Minister that unless
                    there are American interests involved of which I am not now advised I shall be
                    glad to support the desire of Norway to extend sovereignty over Spitzbergen in
                    the event that the status of the archipelago becomes a subject of discussion
                    here. Lansing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
